    "reasoning": "The problem requires implementing a PS/2 mouse protocol message boundary detector using a finite state machine.\n\nKey requirements:\n1. Messages are 3 bytes long\n2. First byte of each message has in[3] = 1\n3. We discard bytes until we see in[3] = 1, then count 3 bytes\n4. Signal 'done' = 1 in the cycle immediately after the third byte is received\n5. Reset is active high synchronous\n\nFSM Design:\n- IDLE state: Searching for in[3] = 1 (potential start of message)\n- GOT1 state: Received byte 1 (the one with in[3] = 1), waiting for byte 2\n- GOT2 state: Received byte 2, waiting for byte 3\n- GOT3 state: Received byte 3, signal done = 1, then return to IDLE\n\nState transitions:\n- IDLE: If in[3] = 1, go to GOT1; else stay in IDLE\n- GOT1: Always go to GOT2 (receive byte 2)\n- GOT2: Always go to GOT3 (receive byte 3)\n- GOT3: Go to IDLE (message complete)\n\nOutput:\n- done = 1 only in GOT3 state (cycle after third byte received)\n- done = 0 in all other states\n\nAdvice to avoid syntax errors:\n- Use localparam for state definitions (not state_t)\n- Declare all signals as logic\n- Use always @(*) for combinational logic\n- Use always @(posedge clk) for sequential logic\n- Avoid 'inside', 'unique', 'unique0' operators",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input logic clk,\n    input logic reset,\n    input logic [7:0] in,\n    output logic done\n);\n\n    localparam IDLE = 2'b00;\n    localparam GOT1 = 2'b01;\n    localparam GOT2 = 2'b10;\n    localparam GOT3 = 2'b11;\n\n    logic [1:0] state;\n    logic [1:0] state_next;\n\n    // Sequential logic for state register\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset)\n            state <= IDLE;\n        else\n            state <= state_next;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational next state logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        state_next = state;\n        case (state)\n            IDLE: begin\n                if (in[3])\n                    state_next = GOT1;\n                else\n                    state_next = IDLE;\n            end\n            GOT1: state_next = GOT2;\n            GOT2: state_next = GOT3;\n            GOT3: state_next = IDLE;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Combinational output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            GOT3: done = 1'b1;\n            default: done = 1'b0;\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
